text.section:
To facilitate the rehabilitation, liquidation, conservation, or dissolution of an insurer under this subtitle, the Commissioner, subject to the approval of the court, may:
borrow money;
execute, acknowledge, and deliver notes or other evidences of indebtedness for the loan;
secure the repayment of the loan by the mortgage, pledge, assignment, or transfer in trust of all or part of the property of the insurer; and
take any other action necessary and proper to consummate the loan and to provide for its repayment.
